The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Sharath to play in Madrid 

New Delhi: After becoming the first Indian table tennis player to reach the semi-finals of a ITTF pro-tour event, Achanta Sharath Kamal is looking to raise his game a few notches by playing for the elite San Sebastian club in Madrid. 

Sharath Kamal has been roped in by the super division Spanish club for eight months from mid-September. He would represent San Sebastian in Spanish and meets abroad. 

It should be a very good experience for me at San Sebastian. I have heard a lot about the club and there are some good players, Kamal said from Patiala. (PTI) 




